Hypothesis Testing about a Population Variance (3 of 12)
Hypotheses
\[
\begin{aligned}
H_0 &: \sigma^2 \leq \sigma^2_0 \\
H_a &: \sigma^2 &gt; \sigma^2_0 \quad \text{(Right-tailed)}
\end{aligned}
\]
where \(\sigma^2_0\) is the hypothesized value for the population variance.
Test Statistic
\[
\chi^2 = \frac{(n-1)S^2}{\sigma^2_0}
\]

Hypothesis Testing about a Population Variance (5 of 12)
Hypotheses
\[
\begin{aligned}
H_0 &: \sigma^2 = \sigma^2_0 \\
H_a &: \sigma^2 \neq \sigma^2_0 \quad \text{(Two-tailed)}
\end{aligned}
\]
where \(\sigma^2_0\) is the hypothesized value for the population variance.
Test Statistic
\[
\chi^2 = \frac{(n-1)S^2}{\sigma^2_0}
\]

